      About this item

      • Customizable YISEELE alarm system - The kit includes an alarm base station, 10 contact sensors for windows/doors, 1 anti-pet motion detector for hallways/rooms and 2 remote controls with a siren ( 120DB)
      • Alarm system with Dual Band Wi-Fi: YISEELE alarm works with dual band 2.4 GHz or 5 GHz Wi-Fi. You can turn on your phone's Bluetooth to find available networks to connect to 2.4 GHz or 5 GHz Wi-Fi. All accessories in the set are factory matched
      • Voice Control - Alexa compatible home alarm system via APP. Away, Disarm and Home modes can be easily controlled by voice hands-free
      • Covers the whole Room - The motion sensor detects activity within 12 feet, it has a 90-degree field of view, and gets along well with pets up to 50 lbs. Perfectly covers the entire room when placed in a corner
      • DIY Installation- A great fit for condos and apartments. No matter where you are, you can change the security mode and manage your devices on the APP. Feel free to add other components, such as door sensor, PIR, solar wireless sound and light siren , water sense, doorbell, smoke sense, etc.
      • Wireless Door sensor detects - Uses HALL technology to minimize false alarms. The signal range is wide enough to reach every corner of most houses
      • Personalize your home security - Customize your wireless house alarm system in the APP, how your sensors protect your home, and choose your favorite accessory mode for your alarm
      • APP Notifications for Siren - 120 decibel siren helps deter intruders. Check in from anywhere in the world and receive real-time alerts and notifications when wireless house alarms are triggered from your smartphone
      • Alarm base indicator light - When the sensor is triggered, the house alarms security system will emit a 120DB alarm sound. At the same time, the base will emit a red indicator light to indicate that there is an intruder

      Product Description

      YISEELE Alarm System for Home Security, Wi-Fi Door Alarms for Safety with APP Alert (2.4GHz and 5GHz Wifi), Wireless 16-Piece kit: HUB, Door Sensors, Anti-pet PIR, Remotes, work with Alexa

      • YISEELE door alarms for home security supports 2.4GHz and 5GHz frequency signals:
      • No need to switch networks, you can connect to wifi directly, applicable to 2.4GHz and 5GHz dual-band wifi
      • Don't worry about the problem that you can't switch the network and can't connect to the alarm system
      • It supports 5GHz wifi and its network is smoother. Don't worry about the problem of being unable to connect to the network after a certain period of use

      Support Assistant:

      • arm my home in armed mode.
      • arm my house.
      • disarm my home.
      • is my house armed?

      (my home) can be customized in the APP

      Alexa voice system support:

      • Alexa, arm my home in armed mode.
      • Alexa, arm my home.
      • Alexa, disarm my home.
      • Alexa, is my house armed?

      (my home) can be customized in the APP

      Anti-Pet motion sensor (PIR) specification:

      • Operating Voltage: DC 3V (2 AA LR6 AM3 1.5V AA battery, including)
      • Detecting Range: 4 meters. Detector Size: 107mm*52mm*41mm/4.21*2.05*1.61"
      • Installation Height: 2.0m-2.2m
      • Pet Immune: Max. 20kg

      Window/Door Sensor

      • Fix the window/door sensor to the door (2 side), and make sure when the door or window are closed, they can be leaned together. If the doors or windows are opened, the 2 parts of the door sensor are separately, then it will send single to the base station ( alarm system) to trigger the alarm and then send alert to your phone

      Wired Siren

      • At 120dbs, this siren will not only alert the neighbors of the intrusion, but scare away the burglar right out of your house! No intruder will hang around when one of these sirens sounds

      Remote control

      • Remote control is a device conducting various functional operation through wireless to facilitate the user to control outdoors or indoors. It conducts operation of outdoor arming, indoor arming, SOS and disarming on the alarm host

      Timing arming and disarming function:

      • You can set the timing start function of arming, disarming, arming at home, SOS and other functions in the APP. After reaching the set time, the system will automatically start this function. More than 20 groups of timing functions can be set

      Three light modes of YISEELE alarm system:

      1. Night light mode: the Hub emtis blue light
      2. Alarm mode: the Hub emits red light
      3. Low battery reminder: the Hub emits orange right

      Four alarm modes:

      1. Disarmed:

      • No accessories are monitored except for those whose attributes are 24H

      2. Armed:

      • All accessories are monitored to protect the home

      3. Home:

      • Accessories whose attributes are "home" are not tracked

      4. SOS:

      • Immediately raise an alarm in an emergency

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • Michael G
        5.0 out of 5 stars Works quite well-simple setup
        Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        The media could not be loaded.
        I was really pleasantly surprised at the build quality and overall ease and simplicity of the setup process. Installation was also fairly simple and straightforward, although I ran into an issue installing sensors on two steel clad doors. After some troubleshooting, it appeared that the steel door skin was interfering with the magnetic component of the door switch. I was able to overcome this by making a simple shim out of a piece of scrap wood flooring, attaching that to the door itself and then attaching the smaller component of the switch assembly to the shim. Please see the attached photos and video for additional detail. The app is surprisingly simple and once you’ve become accustomed to it, it’s easy to use and has a lot of functionality. I don’t intended to purchase the monitoring service so I’m satisfied with how this performs as a stand alone system . The only negative comment I’ll make is that the included USB power and the external siren power cords are both entirely too short which really limits where you can install the main hub. I chose the only elevated electrical receptacle I have on my first floor and it worked perfectly. I originally attempted to locate the hub elsewhere, but the power cord was so short the hub, if wall mounted would have been below wall switch height.

      • Al
        5.0 out of 5 stars A great functional alarm system
        Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 9, 2024
        Verified Purchase
        This is the 3rd wireless alarm system that I have purchased and installed over the last 10 years. The Yiseele alarm costs about a third in price of the previous two, which relied on expensive lead-acid batteries for backup.

        The Yiseele alarm system relies on the tuya smart app, which is available to download for free from the usual app stores. I have found the tuya app to be easy to use and configure, just be sure to create a strong password and keep a record of it. You can create sub accounts through the app, which can then be used by others to arm or disarm the system. Unlike my previous alarm systems, there is no physical control or keypad on the alarm itself, so you need to use the app or the supplied keyfobs for arming/disarming the system.

        The system comes very well packaged, and includes everything you need to get started. In my experience, all the door/window/pir sensors were configured to the actual alarm and all I had to do was identify which physical sensor matched the device id (you can do this by simply setting off each sensor and noting which device was triggered in the app (then mark the id on the back of the sensor). You can rename each device in the app (Front Door etc) for easier identification. If you purchase further add on sensors they can be added via the app.

        Before starting to install the system, its worth looking at the video on YouTube which guides you through the process. A booklet in English is provided in the box if you don't want to bother with the video.

        The alarm that I purchased came with 10 door/window sensors, a pet friendly pir sensor and an internal siren which connects to the alarm. The alarm itself has its own siren, but the separate one is much louder. All the sensors come with batteries installed and with good quality double sided stickers for attaching to the various doors and windows. You need to drill a couple of holes for the alarm, siren and the pir, but the screws and wall plugs are included. A nice touch is that the door/window sensors can also be setup through the app as a door bell. I tested this and it works very well. The alarm has a built in clock and night light, but I have them turned off via the app as they are not required. The alarm has several lights on the front indicating the alarm and power status. The sensors and alarms have anti-tamper built in as well. The power is provided by a usb charger, which also comes in the box (I swopped this out for a slimline one due to the location of my alarm). If you get a power fail the tuya app will trigger an alarm.

        If you want the alarm to warn the neighbours of an activation, you will need to purchase the external solar siren. Things like this depend on your reason for fitting the alarm in the first place, but for me, I'm happy with the internal siren and app notifications when out and about.

        I have been using the system for a few weeks now, and have not had any false alarms or problems. The pir sensor has worked well and the cat has not set it off as yet! My advice is to take a little time to read the information, and to have a good look at the tuya app before starting the installation.

        Price and performance wise, this system is a real bargain and I do not hesitate to give it a 5 ***** review. I will be using this alarm system as my go to setup when replacing systems in the future for family and friends.
